    <template id="watch_routine_care_page" name="Routine Care for Your Watch">
        <t t-call="website.layout">
            <div class="oe_structure">
                <section class="as-offer-services pt32 pb32">
                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="seaction-head">
                            <h1>Routine Care for Your Watch</h1>
                        </div>
                        <div class="seaction-head-desc">
                            <p class="o_default_snippet_text">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-lg-4">
                                <div class="service-box">
                                    <div class="icon">
                                        <span class="fa fa-stopwatch" style="" />
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="service-inner">
                                        <h2>Setting Your Watch</h2>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            Setting the time on your watch is simple, remove your watch from your wrist then pull the crown out (unscrew it first if necessary) and turn it to move the hands forward. But, of course, there are caveats…
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <br />
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">If your watch has a manual winding mechanism, we advise you to wind it every day at the same time so that the mainspring is kept sufficiently taut.</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <br />
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            If you do not use it for a while, wind your mechanical watch (self-winding or manual-winding) at least once a month. For a manual-winding watch, turn the crown until it resists further winding, without
                                            forcing it. For a self-winding watch, we recommend at least 25 turns of the crown. This will help to keep the movement components well lubricated.
                                        </p>
                                        <p class="o_default_snippet_text" style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <br />
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Set the watch forward rather than running it backward:</b>
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            As a general practice, for mechanical watches, set the time by rolling it forward, rather than backward. While some modern watches can withstand both directions, for most, the mechanisms are designed around
                                            moving forward, so some can’t take the stress of reversing. Also, after a mechanical watch settles in, reversing the watch against the pattern of normal wear may cause unnecessary additional wear. One general
                                            rule is that if your mechanical watch's second-hand doesn’t stop when you put the watch in time setting mode, then you should definitely not turn the hands backward.
                                        </p>
                                        <p class="o_default_snippet_text" style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <br />
                                        </p>
                                        <p class="o_default_snippet_text" style="text-align: justify;">Avoid setting the date and time between 9 pm to 3 am (on the watch)</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">The date mechanism is activated during these hours, so setting the date when the watch is in this time frame can damage the movement's gears and pinions.&amp;nbsp;</p>
                                        <div class="btn-block">
                                            <a href="/watch-service-guide">Return to Watch Service Guide</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-lg-4">
                                <div class="service-box">
                                    <div class="icon">
                                        <span class="fa fa-broom" style="" />
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="service-inner">
                                        <h2>Cleaning Your Watch</h2>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">Keeping your watch clean on the outside lessens the chance of it getting dirty on the inside. Wipe off your watch periodically to remove dust, dirt, moisture, and perspiration.</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <br />
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Water-resistant watches:</b>
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">- Use a soft damp cloth to clean the head of the watch.</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">- Then wipe it off with a dry soft cloth.</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">- Metal bracelets can be cleaned by using mild soapy water and a soft toothbrush.</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <br />
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <b>Non-water resistant watches:</b>
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">- Avoid exposure to any moisture.</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">- Simply wipe the watch with a dry soft cloth.</p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">- Leather straps should be kept dry and conditioned occasionally, as you would any fine leather good.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</p>
                                        <div class="btn-block">
                                            <a href="/watch-service-guide">Return to Watch Service Guide</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-lg-4">
                                <div class="service-box">
                                    <div class="icon">
                                        <span class="fa fa-calendar-check" style="" />
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="service-inner">
                                        <h2>Maintenance Schedules</h2>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">To maintain your watch in the best working order, refer to our suggested maintenance schedules.&amp;nbsp;</p>
                                        <div class="btn-block">
                                            <a href="/watch-maintenance-schedules">Go to Watch Maintenance Schedules</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
            </div>
        </t>
    </template>

    <template id="watch_water_resistance_page" name="Water Resistance">
        <t t-call="website.layout">
            <div class="oe_structure">
                <section class="as-offer-services pt32 pb32">
                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="seaction-head">
                            <h1>Water Resistance</h1>
                        </div>
                        <div class="seaction-head-desc">
                            <p class="o_default_snippet_text" style="text-align: justify;">
                                Not all watches are designed to be water-resistant, and even when they are, the degree of water resistance varies. Also, remember that water resistance isn't a permanent condition. The gaskets and seals used to seal the
                                watch deteriorate over time and need to be replaced occasionally. So be sure to have your watch tested and its water-resistance restored periodically.
                            </p>
                            <p class="o_default_snippet_text" style="text-align: justify;">
                                <br />
                            </p>
                            <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                <b>Water-resistance defined:</b>
                            </p>
                            <p style="text-align: justify;">3 ATM / 30 m<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>Protected against perspiration and accidental splashes of water, but avoid submerging it in water.</p>
                            <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                5 ATM / 50 m<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>Protected against light use in water. It can be suitable for swimming, but not high impact water activities, like high diving or water skiing.
                            </p>
                            <p style="text-align: justify;">10 ATM / 100 m<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>The watch has a high degree of water resistance. It can be suitable for snorkeling, but not scuba diving.</p>
                            <p style="text-align: justify;">20 ATM / 200 m<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>The watch can be worn while scuba diving, but it is not a professional divers’ watch.</p>
                            <p style="text-align: justify;">30 ATM / 300 m<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>The watch can be worn while deep water diving and can withstand repeated use as a professional divers’ watch.</p>
                            <div>
                                <br />
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-lg-4">
                                <div class="service-box">
                                    <div class="icon">
                                        <span class="fa fa-water" style="" />
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="service-inner">
                                        <h2>Have your watch tested every 12−18 months</h2>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            How frequently you should test your watch depends on how often you wear it and in what conditions. A variety of factors can impact the seals, such as UV light, cosmetics, salt water, hot tubs, saunas, or
                                            heavy shocks. Have it tested annually and the seals replaced when necessary.
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="btn-block">
                                            <a href="/watch-service-guide" data-original-title="" title="" aria-describedby="tooltip382211">Return to Watch Service Guide</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-lg-4">
                                <div class="service-box">
                                    <div class="icon">
                                        <span class="fa fa-crown" style="" />
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="service-inner">
                                        <h2>Always secure the screw-down crown</h2>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">
                                            If your watch is designed for water activities, be sure the crown is pushed down or screwed in tightly before wearing it in water. Then while in a wet environment, do not operate or adjust the crown and/or
                                            push buttons as water can seep into the case.
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="btn-block">
                                            <a href="/watch-service-guide">Return to Watch Service Guide</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-lg-4">
                                <div class="service-box">
                                    <div class="icon">
                                        <span class="fa fa-broom" style="" />
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="service-inner">
                                        <h2>Clean your watch after water use, in the sea and pools especially</h2>
                                        <p class="o_default_snippet_text" style="text-align: justify;">Rinse the watch with clean water after swimming or diving with it. This will eliminate any dirt and chemicals from the pool or ocean.</p>
                                        <p class="o_default_snippet_text" style="text-align: justify;">
                                            <br />
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="text-align: justify;">If the watch has a rotating bezel, be sure to rotate the bezel while cleaning to dislodge any debris (sand or salt).</p>
                                        <div class="btn-block">
                                            <a href="/watch-service-guide">Return to Watch Service Guide</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
